Sissy Winn is a renowned rodeo contestant and barrel racer who has made a significant impact in the world of rodeo. Born on January 5, 1998, in Chapman Ranch, Texas, Winn has been around horses her entire life and has been competing in rodeo events since her junior high and high school years.

She has been a two-time National Finals Rodeo (NFR) qualifier in 2022 and 2023 and has earned a reputation for her skill, determination, and passion for the sport.

Here we have Sissy Winn’s net worth, career earnings, professional career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Sissy Winn

Sissy Winn was born and raised in Chapman Ranch, Texas. She is the daughter of Tom and Melissa Winn and has an older sister named Amy.

Winn’s family has been instrumental in her rodeo career, providing support and encouragement as she pursued her dreams. She was named after an aunt who passed away.

Winn’s love for horses and rodeo was evident from a young age. In junior high and high school, she competed in various rodeo events, including barrel racing, breakaway roping, goat tying, cutting, and pole bending.

She was a seven-time national qualifier for junior high and high school finals and won the 2013 Texas High School Rodeo Association All-Around cowgirl title.

Early Life

Sissy Winn’s early life was steeped in rodeo culture. She and her sister Amy shared horses and competed in every rodeo event offered to young girls in southern Texas.

Winn’s dedication to the sport was evident, and she began working towards her NFR goals while studying at Texas A&M University in College Station. She graduated Magna Cum Laude with a degree in Agricultural Leadership and Development.

Professional Career

Winn’s professional career took off when she qualified for her first National Finals Rodeo in 2022. She has since become a two-time NFR qualifier (2022-2023) and has won numerous rodeo events, including the Walker County Fair & Rodeo, Langley BC Rodeo, and the Rodeo Corpus Christi in 2023.

Sissy Winn’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, the estimated net worth of Sissy Winn is $1 million.

She has earned significant income from her rodeo career. In 2023 alone, she earned over $387,920 in the regular season.

Career Earnings

Sissy Winn’s career earnings through the 2023 regular season amounted to $387,920, with her 2023 earnings being $109,022. These earnings come from her winnings at various rodeo events and competitions.

Personal Details

Boyfriend

As of 2023, Sissy Winn is reported to be single. She is currently focusing on her career only.

How Old is Sissy Winn?

Sissy Winn was born on January 5, 1998, making her 25 years old as of 2023.

What is her nationality?

She is American.

FAQs About Sissy Winn 

When was she born?

She was born on January 5, 1998.

What is Sissy Winn’s net worth?

Her estimated net worth is $1 million.

Who are her endorsers?

She is endorsed by Simply Equine and SUCCEED, both of which are companies in the equine industry.
